><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Xbox Series X]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Xbox Series X]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[WhatsApp adds Telegram-style video messages]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>现在，您可以轻松地向您的 WhatsApp 好友展示您在做什么，而无需花费精力创建故事或类似剪辑。该服务正在<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://blog.whatsapp.com/introducing-instant-video-messages">推出</a>类似于 Telegram 的即时视频消息，让您可以在聊天中用长达一分钟的视频进行回复。您只需点击并按住按钮即可拍摄素材，然后向上滑动即可在放手的情况下继续录制。</p><p>视频会自动静音播放，因此在您准备好点击打开声音之前，不要吓到任何人。与 WhatApp 中的大多数其他内容一样，即时消息经过端到端加密，以增加一层隐私。该公司表示，该功能将在“未来几周”内向所有用户开放。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>对于很多人来说，这可能不会取代 Telegram Snapchat。 WhatsApp 在消息传递领域仍然占据主导地位，并且主要由电话和短信驱动。即便如此，如果您不想只是为了发送快速视频而切换应用程序，那么该功能可能会受到赞赏。当文本或音频消息无法解决问题时，您可以快速分享新闻，或者只是用比贴纸更个性化的东西来回应朋友。</p><p>母公司 Meta 有采取行动的动力。截至去年，WhatsApp 拥有超过 20 亿活跃用户，而 Telegram 正在迅速扩张，每月活跃用户<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.thinkimpact.com/telegram-statistics/#:~:text=Telegram%20has%20an%20estimated%20700,and%20sits%20right%20behind%20Snapchat.">估计</a>达 7 亿。尽管来自其他社交平台的激烈竞争<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/snapchat-already-has-3-million-subscribers-172021014.html">，Snapchat 仍在增长</a>。苹果的 iOS 17 还将向 iPhone 用户引入<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ios-17-preview-public-beta-facetime-standby-iphone-120025938.html">FaceTime 视频语音邮件</a>。虽然即时视频消息可能无法说服用户注册，但它可能会阻止 WhatsApp 粉丝转向竞争对手。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/whatsapp-adds-telegram-style-video-messages-141005605.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/whatsapp-adds-telegram-style-video-messages-141005605.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 1a778c06-79cc-47ae-9a4e-35dbfc123396</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 28 Jul 2023 14:10:05 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690553407</ingested><modified> 2023-07-28T14:10:12+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/6ad5a110-2d46-11ee-9bfd-9b96e1f1fb89" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/6ad5a110-2d46-11ee-9bfd-9b96e1f1fb89" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Meta]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[WhatsApp instant video messages]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[WhatsApp instant video messages]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best SSDs for the PS5]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> PlayStation 5 上架十个月后，索尼<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sony-ps-5-ssd-storage-expansion-firmware-update-ps4-remote-play-135032853.html">发布了软件更新</a>，解锁了游戏机的存储扩展插槽。最初，PS5 只提供 667GB 的空间来存储游戏，而且无法增加。虽然这对一些游戏玩家（比如我）来说没什么问题，但其他人（比如我儿子）却被迫执行近乎日常的杂耍行为，其中包括频繁删除和重新下载游戏，因为控制台的 SSD 存储空间较低，并且显然需要不断地更新游戏。访问所有《使命召唤》游戏。</p><p>现在，您可以通过安装标准 PCIe Gen4 x4 M.2 NVMe SSD 来增加 PS5 的可用存储空间。如果那些乱七八糟的首字母缩略词让你感到畏缩，别担心，你会发现它并没有那么复杂，如果你想知道哪些是最适合你的 PS5 的 SSD，你可以跳到我们的最后首选。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2>我需要多少存储空间？ </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-11/341eb080-1ec1-11eb-bffb-88f330aaaf35" alt="索尼 PlayStation 5 游戏机。" data-uuid="a2d26540-68ec-3e38-a70e-59b044befdb5"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">亚伦·索普里斯/Engadget</div></figure><p> PS5 将接受容量在 250GB 到 4TB 之间的驱动器。如果您已经拥有 PlayStation 5，那么您很可能对游戏库需要多少存储空间有一个合理的了解。如果您为新 PS5 购买 SSD，或者为其他人购买，则很难判断您可能需要什么才能获得高性能体验。</p><p> PS5 游戏平均比 PS4 游戏要小一些，通常占用 30GB 到 100GB 之间，但也有一些值得注意（且非常流行）的例外。如果您是《使命召唤》系列的粉丝，安装<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/mwii-modern-warfare-ii-warzone-2-no-russian-170044023.html"><em>《现代战争 II》</em>和<em>《战区</em><em>2.0》</em></a>将需要超过 200GB。换句话说，完整的《使命召唤》安装将占用 PS5 内部存储空间的近三分之一。不过，如果您不是 CoD 粉丝，那么在遇到问题之前，您可能会在 PS5 内部存储 6 到 10 个游戏。</p><p>另一件需要考虑的事情是您的互联网速度。如果您居住在宽带速度较慢的地区，“您可以再次下载”的理由并不真正有效。在我的老家，下载一个 100GB 的文件大约需要 8 个小时，在此期间我很难同时观看 Twitch，或者发布有关升级 PS5 SSD 的文章。如果您偶尔想玩游戏，那么保留游戏是有意义的。</p><p>乍一看，购买 250GB 驱动器基本上没有意义。从经济上来说，250GB 驱动器并不比 500GB 驱动器便宜多少，而且实际上，对于现代游戏来说，这确实没有太多的生存空间。 500GB 驱动器的价格约为 80 至 140 美元，是一个不错的选择，但对大多数人来说，最好的选择是选择 1TB 驱动器，其价格应在 160 至 250 美元之间。这将使您可用于游戏的空间增加一倍以上，而无需花太多钱。 （作为比较，希捷官方 1TB Xbox 系列扩展卡的售价为<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9TZWFnYXRlLVN0b3JhZ2UtRXhwYW5zaW9uLVNvbGlkLVN0YXRlL2RwL0IwOEszUzZXSk0_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8taWstMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImU3NTEzM2RjLThjMTYtNDU5Yi05YmY4LTZmMzg5MmNkN2M3NyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAWYqA3XdwtIAt__AJTdDj3gF3vqXWgBTdsRt5Of1gaGN&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSeagate-Storage-Expansion-Solid-State%2Fdp%2FB08K3S6WJM">220 美元</a>。）</p><p>如果您有钱，2TB 驱动器有时会带来每 GB 的边际节省，并且通常可以在其他型号缺货时找到。除非您有大量现金并且想要灵活使用，否则大多数情况下应避免使用 4TB 型号，因为您最终为每 GB 支付的费用将高于 1TB 或 2TB 驱动器。</p><p>最后一点：虽然 825GB PS5 仅提供 667GB 存储空间，但这很大程度上是因为为操作系统和缓存保留了存储空间。如果您安装 1TB SSD，则在误差范围内，您将拥有 1TB 的可用存储空间用于游戏。</p><h2>可以在外接 SSD 上玩 PS5 游戏吗？ </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-08/f9a78850-01b4-11ec-bdf1-6047ddc9fc71" alt="三星T5 SSD" data-uuid="efd7a126-1843-30c4-8265-f32639c0d1ab"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">三星</div></figure><p>它们的价格比高端内置 SSD 低得多，但它们的用途受到限制。外部 SSD 通过 USB 连接到 PS5，仅适合玩 PS4 游戏或存储 PS5 游戏。如果您除了最好的互联网之外什么都没有，那么这很有用——将 PS5 游戏从外部驱动器上的“冷存储”中移出比重新下载它更快——或者只是想要大量的 PS4 游戏。</p><p>由于此处的限制，您不需要最高性能的型号，但您应该选择 SSD 而不是 HDD 以提高传输速度和加载时间。任何知名品牌的基本便携式硬盘都可以，我们已经尝试过并可以推荐 Crucial X6 和 Samsung T5。</p><h2> PS5兼容SSD卡</h2><h2></h2><p>这个问题的官方答案是“M.2 Socket 3 (Key M) Gen4 x4 NVME SSD”。但即使在看似具体的描述中，仍然有更多的事情需要考虑。索尼对兼容性提出的主要要求归结为速度、冷却和物理尺寸。</p><p>对于速度， <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:PlayStation;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=0f845666-5cc0-42c7-863d-d873ae1b6087&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=PlayStation&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAc8uKbsYWnTQxryFbJ-m42NXSvrXAQQXVa430BYLCdUs&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.playstation.com%2Fen-us%2Fsupport%2Fhardware%2Fps5-install-m2-ssd%2F%23min">索尼表示</a>驱动器应该能够以 5,500MB/s 的速度处理顺序读取。早期测试表明，PS5 可接受低至 4,800MB/s 的驱动器，并且经常使用 SSD 的游戏（例如<em>《瑞奇与叮当：裂痕</em>》）不会造成任何问题。 PS5 唯一会彻底拒绝的东西几乎就是不符合 Gen4 x4 规格的东西。</p><p>不过，我们认为，使用比规格慢的驱动器是有风险的，如果您还没有该驱动器，则不值得冒险。仅仅因为我们还没有发现问题，并不意味着以后不会有游戏出现问题。这些稍慢的 Gen4 驱动器与符合索尼规格的驱动器之间的价格差异并不大，您也可以覆盖所有基础。</p><p>比速度稍微复杂的是冷却和尺寸。大多数裸 SSD 就可以了； PS5 几乎可以容纳任何长度的 22 毫米宽 SSD（准确地说是 30 毫米、42 毫米、60 毫米、80 毫米或 110 毫米）。您发现的绝大多数驱动器都是 22 毫米宽、80 毫米长，所以没有问题。</p><p>应该注意的是，该系统可以安装 25 毫米宽的驱动器，但该宽度必须包括冷却解决方案。说到这里，索尼表示 SSD 需要“通过散热器等冷却结构进行有效散热”。索尼插槽支持的最大高度为11.25毫米，其中只有2.45毫米可以位于驱动器“下方”。这意味着一些最流行的散热 Gen4 SSD，包括 Corsair 的 MP600 Pro LPX 和 Sabrent 的 Rocket 4 Plus，无法安装在 PS5 的存储扩展插槽中。自 Engadget 于 2021 年首次发布本指南以来，包括三星在内的大多数 NVMe 制造商都推出了 PlayStation 专用型号来考虑这些因素。</p><p>也就是说，如果你想省点钱，裸机通常要便宜得多，而且找到适用于 PS5 的冷却解决方案也很简单。</p><p> NVMe SSD 中唯一真正需要冷却的组件是控制器，如果没有散热器，它会很高兴地烤一块（非常小的）牛排。大多数 SSD 仅在一侧有芯片，但即使在双面 SSD 上，控制器也可能位于顶部，因为制造商知道它需要放置在那里以更好地散热。因此，前往您选择的 PC 组件销售商，购买基本上符合建议尺寸的任何产品。一个很好的搜索术语是“笔记本电脑 NVME 散热器”，因为它们的设计适合游戏笔记本电脑的限制，而游戏笔记本电脑的限制甚至比 PS5 还要严格。它们通常也比标有“PS5 散热器”的产品便宜。</p><p>其中一项推荐是这款<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAXHHVFCgcP2am_p2O047u4wyz1ldvhuDHiQrDg4n61Nr&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FHeatsink-Copper-Copper%25EF%25BC%258C-Silicone-Thermal%2Fdp%2FB07QNRP9HK%3F">价值 7 美元的铜散热器</a>，它通过粘性热界面材料连接到 SSD。它工作得很好，而且实际上，在电脑上进行压力测试时，我们找不到任何不能控制温度的金属。当您进行搜索时，只需确保您选择的解决方案的宽度不超过 25 毫米，高度不超过 8 毫米（包括热界面材料），并且安装方法简单，不会造成任何麻烦。</p><p>现在，如果所有这些都非常无聊，这里有一些现成的建议：</p><h2>最佳 PS5 SSD：Corsair MP600 Pro LPX</h2><p><core-commerce id="83b8c77555954122aa2ab7edf84eb40d" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlRMk1XMjFGP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWlrLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJlNzUxMzNkYy04YzE2LTQ1OWItOWJmOC02ZjM4OTJjZDdjNzcifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAcyTGBC9fwwm7DX2Oq2ZLPIcMU6xWzj9ECB35LQMD6_r&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09Q2MW21F">Corsair MP600</a> Pro LPX 在我们检查所有选项的列表中名列前茅。它速度很快，读取速度高达 7,100MB/s，并配有预装散热器。它还提供五年保修。最重要的是，MP600 价格实惠。最近几个月，1TB 型号的售价不到 100 美元（尽管通常售价为 185 美元），而 2TB 型号的售价约为 210 美元。</p><h2>最实惠的 PS5 SSD：Crucial P5 Plus</h2><p><core-commerce id="e4e8c50bed3c4de1b1cafe1c51918f6e" data-type="product-list"></p><p>如果您想通过安装自己的散热器来节省一点钱， <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDk4V0w0NlJTP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWlrLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJlNzUxMzNkYy04YzE2LTQ1OWItOWJmOC02ZjM4OTJjZDdjNzcifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAVHvCkzH7Gm5C66C1tyv1WkvUDGPY49hMzy5Bi1HgBfn&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB098WL46RS%3F">Crucial P5 Plus NVMe</a>是一个经济实惠的选择。 P5 Plus 的读取速度高达 6,600MB/s，仅比我们的首选慢一点，并且在打折时您经常可以以低至 80 美元的价格找到 1TB 型号。预计 2TB 版本打折时售价约为 180 美元。</p><h2>另一个不错的选择：三星 980 Pro</h2><p><core-commerce id="225f55a86ee64afea030ae9daf9b0f51" data-type="product-list"></p><p>如果您不熟悉 Crucial 英睿达或 Corsair 等公司，并且想要选择更知名的品牌，那么 NVMe 领域没有比三星更大的厂商了。该公司最近开始销售其备受推崇的<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlKSEwzM1g3P3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWlrLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJlNzUxMzNkYy04YzE2LTQ1OWItOWJmOC02ZjM4OTJjZDdjNzcifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAWn9t4ys6TOvV1Pgp-bGOE7PNmPDYrCWehid7Bu7LYCz&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09JHL33X7">980 Pro SSD</a>的散热版本。它比此列表中的其他一些 NVMe 驱动器更贵，但也不是很贵。 1TB 型号的预计售价约为 230 美元（促销时售价约为 110 美元），2TB 型号的预计售价为 200 美元。</p><h2><strong>另一个不错的选择：</strong> Sabrent Rocket 4 Plus</h2><p><core-commerce id="b396141871764599a62418655116452e" data-type="product-list"></p><p>在此列表中的所有 SSD 中， <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlHMk1aNFZSP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWlrLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJlNzUxMzNkYy04YzE2LTQ1OWItOWJmOC02ZjM4OTJjZDdjNzcifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAc7zgp3E8aAP8Pi8F53B0GQNxpyiEZ9KHPvd5TP2ttUM&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09G2MZ4VR%3F">Sabrent Rocket 4 Plus</a>是最有趣的。它配备了一个独特的散热器，您可以将其安装在存储扩展槽金属盖的位置。 Sabrent 声称这种设计提高了冷却性能。定价与三星的产品一致，1TB 型号的价格约为 160 美元，2TB 型号的价格为 300 美元。</p><h2><strong>另一个不错的选择：</strong> PNY XLR8</h2><p><core-commerce id="765e0e0fd322476ab7d0c08636270d4c" data-type="product-list"></p><p>如果 Sabrent 的设计对您有吸引力，但在寻找时找不到价格合适的 Rocket 4 Plus，PNY 提供了类似的冷却解决方案，其 PS5 版本的<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlZTjZRQzY1P3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWlrLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJlNzUxMzNkYy04YzE2LTQ1OWItOWJmOC02ZjM4OTJjZDdjNzcifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAV6HF2Gyua93qBbhOdacfak3yA-XOIH6FQdtAx5z3-Eu&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09YN6QC65">XLR8 NVMe</a> 。 1TB 型号的售价约为 107 美元。预计 2TB 型号的售价约为 190 美元。</p><h2><strong>另一个不错的选择：</strong> WD Black SN850</h2><p><core-commerce id="8191beca92e14e7b8ece40225ca18994" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWUkqKEffjMp0jz42g4WLvtEENC-v-5iexZGf4HUw6JX&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FWD_BLACK-SN850-Consoles-Solid-Heatsink%2Fdp%2FB0B4SQB1HY%2F">SN850</a>是 PS5 的另一个即插即用选项，提供超过控制台兼容性要求的顺序读取速度，并配有预装散热器。 Western Digital 销售索尼授权的 SN850 型号，有 1TB 和 2TB 两种版本。前者的费用约为 180 美元，而后者的费用约为 300 美元。</p><h2>如何在 PS5 中安装 SSD</h2><p>在尝试向 PS5 添加更多存储空间之前，请确保您已安装索尼的最新软件。一旦您掌握了最新版本，PS5 SSD 的安装就相当简单了。索尼推荐使用 1 号十字螺丝刀或十字螺丝刀，但这并不是什么复杂的事情。任何类似尺寸的十字螺丝刀都可以。</p><p> Begin by powering down your PS5, unplugging everything, removing the stand and flipping it over to its underside. If you have the regular PS5, that&#39;s the side with the disc drive; if you have the Digital Edition, it&#39;s the side without the PlayStation logo cutout.</p><p> Sony has a video guide to popping off the outside cover <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://youtu.be/CaAY-jAjm0w?t=133">here</a> , but the gist is you gently lift up the opposing corners and slide the panel toward the flat end of the console. There&#39;s a knack to this, and it requires very little effort or strength. If you&#39;re not getting it, rather than force it just readjust your grip and try again. A member of our video team managed to break one of the tabs on our review unit doing this in the past so… yeah, don&#39;t force it. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-08/ebf0c2f0-01b7-11ec-afbf-853a752af0d1" alt="Sony PlayStation 5 SSD slot" data-uuid="19f77e94-d5e9-373e-b5ae-8d248dcbb313"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Engadget</div></figure><p> Once you&#39;ve got everything open, you&#39;ll see a rectangular piece of metal with a screw holding it in place. Remove that screw, and you&#39;ll be able to access the drive bay.</p><p> You&#39;ll see five holes inside, each numbered corresponding to the standard SSD drive lengths I mentioned earlier. The one numbered 110 will have a metal insert and screw inside. You need to unscrew the screw with a screwdriver, and then unscrew the insert with your fingers and move it to the relevant hole. Your eyes should tell you which is the right one for your drive, but it&#39;s most likely going to be 80. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-08/e67cea90-01b4-11ec-bbfb-4b7c19b43bb9" alt="PlayStation 5 SSD slot" data-uuid="5af98c48-dea7-375c-bbf7-fbd05e5fba67"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Aaron Souppouris/Engadget</div></figure><p> Then take your SSD — mine is a 980 Pro I bought on Prime Day with a $2 piece of aluminum attached to the top — and slot it in. The slot is at the edge closest to the number “30,” and SSDs are keyed to only fit in one way, so again, no force is required. If it&#39;s not sliding in, don&#39;t force it. You&#39;ll notice the SSD doesn&#39;t sit flat — that&#39;s fine, and is as intended. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-08/cbfb0a40-01b8-11ec-affd-fd9517dd0c1c" alt="Sony PlayStation 5 SSD upgrade" data-uuid="206fc2a7-eaf8-36a0-b225-dde1ea409e37"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Engadget</div></figure><p> Once the SSD is seated, take the screw you removed from the insert, line it up with the little notch at the end of your SSD, and push down so it meets the insert. Give the screw a few turns — it doesn&#39;t need to be very tight — and you&#39;re done. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-08/4dcf1fc0-01b9-11ec-a75f-13723fe12887" alt="Sony PlayStation 5 SSD upgrade" data-uuid="ddd06c56-81d1-36f3-b13e-2ddc9f96daab"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Engadget</div></figure><p> Replace the metal cover and screw it down, and then slide the plastic outer shell back on. When you first turn on the PS5, it&#39;ll prompt you to format the drive. Do that! You have now successfully expanded your console&#39;s storage, and can set about downloading and moving games to it. Personally, I moved all of the PS4 games I had to the new drive, along with all of my clips and screenshots. The PS5&#39;s built-in SSD is always going to be the most compliant, so I&#39;m keeping my important stuff there.</p><p> We&#39;ll be updating this guide as more SSDs come to market and onto our test bench, so feel free to bookmark it for when you need it.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-ps5-ssd-expansion-upgrade-150052315.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-ps5-ssd-expansion-upgrade-150052315.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> e75133dc-8c16-459b-9bf8-6f3892cd7c77</guid><dc:creator> Aaron Souppouris,Igor Bonifacic</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 13:30:28 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690559372</ingested><modified> 2023-07-28T15:49:38+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Computing]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Aaron Souppouris]]></category><media:content height="1621" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-08/e67cea90-01b4-11ec-bbfb-4b7c19b43bb9" width="2560"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1621" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-08/e67cea90-01b4-11ec-bbfb-4b7c19b43bb9" width="2560"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Aaron Souppouris/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[PlayStation 5 SSD slot]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[PlayStation 5 SSD slot]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Tor’s shadowy reputation will only end if we all use it]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> “Tor” evokes an image of the dark web; a place to hire hitmen or buy drugs that, at this point, is overrun by feds trying to catch you in the act. The reality, however, is a lot more boring than that — but it&#39;s also more secure.</p><p> The Onion Router, now called Tor, is a privacy-focused web browser run by a nonprofit group. You can <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.torproject.org/download/">download it for free</a> and use it to shop online or browse social media, just like you would on Chrome or Firefox or Safari, but with additional access to unlisted websites ending in .onion. This is what people think of as the “dark web,” because the sites aren&#39;t indexed by search engines. But those sites aren&#39;t an inherently criminal endeavor.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> “This is not a hacker tool,” said Pavel Zoneff, director of strategic communications at The Tor Project. “It is a browser just as easy to use as any other browser that people are used to.”</p><p> That&#39;s right, despite common misconceptions, Tor can be used for any internet browsing you usually do. The key difference with Tor is that the network hides your IP address and other system information for full anonymity. This may sound familiar, because it&#39;s how a lot of people approach <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-vpn-130004396.html">VPNs</a> , but the difference is in the details.</p><p> VPNs are just encrypted tunnels hiding your traffic from one hop to another. The company behind a VPN can still access your information, sell it or pass it along to law enforcement. With Tor, there&#39;s no link between you and your traffic, according to Jed Crandall, an associate professor at Arizona State University. Tor is built in the “higher layers” of the network and routes your traffic through separate tunnels, instead of a single encrypted tunnel. While the first tunnel may know some personal information and the last one may know the sites you visited, there is virtually nothing connecting those data points because your IP address and other identifying information are bounced from server to server into obscurity.</p><p> In simpler terms: using regular browsers directly connects you and your traffic, adding a VPN routes that information through an encrypted tunnel so that your internet service provider can&#39;t see it and Tor scatters your identity and your search traffic until it becomes almost anonymous, and very difficult to identify.</p><p> Accessing unindexed websites adds extra perks, like secure communication. While a platform like WhatsApp offers encrypted conversations, there could be traces that the conversation happened left on the device if it&#39;s ever investigated, according to Crandall. Tor&#39;s communication tunnels are secure and much harder to trace that the conversation ever happened.</p><p> Other use cases may include keeping the identities of sensitive populations like undocumented immigrants anonymous, trying to unionize a workplace without the company shutting it down, victims of domestic violence looking for resources without their abuser finding out or, as Crandall said, wanting to make embarrassing Google searches without related targeted ads following you around forever.</p><p> Still, with added layers of security can come some additional hiccups, like lag or longer loading times. That could be true for some users depending on what they do online, but anecdotally it&#39;s gotten a lot faster in recent years, and users have said they barely notice a difference compared to other browsers. Sameer Patil, associate professor at the School of Computing at the University of Utah, studied this by having students and staff try out Tor as their main browser. “I was personally very surprised at how many sites and things just work fine in the Tor browser. So not only did they work as intended, but they also were fast enough,” Patil said.</p><p> But even if online privacy isn&#39;t your main concern personally, using Tor can help support industries that heavily rely on it. By using the anonymous and secure browser, you&#39;re supporting activists, journalists and everyone else&#39;s privacy because the more people that use it, the more secure it gets, according to Patil. If only certain sensitive groups use it, it&#39;ll be easier to deanonymize and ultimately track down identities. When you&#39;re one in a billion using it, that task becomes nearly impossible.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/tor-dark-web-privacy-secure-browser-anonymous-130048839.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/tor-dark-web-privacy-secure-browser-anonymous-130048839.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 8bc38b08-7f1f-4a7b-a53f-8d16dac28225</guid><dc:creator> Katie Malone</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 13:00:48 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690548595</ingested><modified> 2023-07-28T12:50:03+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Personal Finance - Career & Education]]></category><category><![CDATA[Internet & Networking Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Katie Malone]]></category><media:content height="3546" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/7049f4a0-25b4-11ee-a7d9-24a07e8b692b" width="5000"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3546" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/7049f4a0-25b4-11ee-a7d9-24a07e8b692b" width="5000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[picture alliance via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[10 December 2021, Baden-Wuerttemberg, Rottweil: The Tor Browser lettering is seen on the display of a MacBook. Photo: Silas Stein/ (Photo by Silas Stein/picture alliance via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Tor Browser]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Engadget Podcast: Samsung’s foldable summer]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Samsung made a huge flex this week by hosting its first Unpacked event in Seoul, South Korea (sorry NYC!). In this episode, Cherlynn, Devindra and Senior Writer Sam Rutherford dive into all of Samsung&#39;s news: The Galaxy Z Fold 5, Z Flip 5, Watch 6 and Tab S9. Is Samsung playing it safe this year, or is it actually bringing something new to the world of foldables? Also, we discuss Twitter&#39;s rebrand to “X” ( <em>sigh</em> ), as well as why astrophysicist Avi Loeb is likely wrong about his extraterrestrial alien balls.</p><p> Listen below or subscribe on your podcast app of choice. If you&#39;ve got suggestions or topics you&#39;d like covered on the show, be sure to <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="mailto:podcast@engadget.com?subject=Engadget%20Podcast%20